<Author>prisonercellblkH
<Content>Spotless and modern The distance from the hotel is about 8 miles but through the traffic takes roughly 20 mins. A taxi will cost around 20 euros and the hotel is well known so there will be no problem in finding it. The hotel itself is situated on a main road, if your room is facing the road you will have a brilliant view of the hussle and bustle of daily life, although the drug drop in centre opposite is a bit seedy looking. There are plenty of shops in the immediate area including a lidl.There wasnt much street noise considering the volume of traffic through the night, there is a thick black curtain which covers the massive window that gives uninteruppted sleep. The rooms themselves are modern- black and white - beautiful really, the shower (big enough for a football team) and toilet all black slate tilesThe rooms are changed daily and the staff are always courteous and wish you a pleasant day.The only down point for me with the hotel and its a minor quibble and thats the room door mechanism - the door can be a nightmare to open, you have to press a button, pass the card pass it wait for a green light,turn handle and hopefully enter - Good luck trying it when you have had a few.When you first exit lindemanns dont go left - theres not a lot there, the main points are all easily reached going right.Word of warning - after dark you will encounter prostitutes on the rroute back to the hotel. They loiter around the bridge 200m away in shorts and long boots - theyre no bother but some may find intimidating.Lindemanns overall is faultless though.. 
